<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="39" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,614,701]" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,269,614,638]" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
—The species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Benth.) Kuntze" authorityName="Kuntze" authorityYear="1891" baseAuthorityName="Bentham" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[569,991,614,637]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Pogostemon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cruciatus">
<emphasis box="[569,808,614,637]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Pogostemon cruciatus</emphasis>
(Benth.) Kuntze
</taxonomicName>
in habit, but differs from the latter in its stems and leaves being whitish adpressed tomentose, leaf margins not revolute and dentate apically, midrib conspicuously elevated, and lateral veins in 3–5 pairs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
