<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,845,1954]" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">
Annual herb, to 
<quantity box="[355,431,845,871]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" unit="cm" value="40.0">40 cm</quantity>
tall. Stem terete, unbranched or rarely branched, straight, erect, striate on lower portion, adpressed whitish tomentose with long hairs. Leaves 4–6-verticellate, sessile; blades elliptic-linear, 
<quantity box="[151,234,922,948]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" unit="cm" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3 cm</quantity>
× 
<quantity box="[266,367,922,948]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" unit="mm" value="5.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="3.0">3–7 mm</quantity>
, apex obtuse, margin not revolute, sometimes dentate apically, base rounded or broadly cuneate, tomentose on both surfaces, hairs unicellular, midrib elevated abaxially, lateral veins 3–5 on each side of midrib. Inflorescence terminal, 
<quantity box="[609,696,1000,1026]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" unit="cm" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7 cm</quantity>
× 
<quantity box="[726,812,1000,1026]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" unit="mm" value="38.0">38 mm</quantity>
, densely flowered, not interrupted, tomentose; bracts linear, villose, longer than the calyx, long-hairy; calyx campanulate, 
<quantity box="[953,1093,1038,1064]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" unit="mm" value="1.65" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.5">1.5–1.8 mm</quantity>
in length, 4-angled and more or less quadrangular, villose outside, lobes 5, subequal; corolla pinkish, very shortly exserted from the calyx tube, lobes oblong, subequal, pubescent outside, corolla tube about 
<quantity box="[941,1008,1116,1142]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
in length; stamens 4, about 
<quantity box="[1338,1405,1116,1142]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
in length, inserted at the mid-part of the corolla tube; filament twice as long as the corolla, joined to the middle of the corolla tube, hairy; anther stalks tapered at the base which is pubescent, bearded at the mid part and more than twice as long as the corolla; anther 1-locular, cell apex dehiscent. Ovary glabrous; stigma shortly bifid at apex. Nutlets not seen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="39" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,845,1954]" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,529,1309,1335]" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Doan ex Gang Yao, Y. F. Deng &amp; X. J. Ge" authorityYear="2013" box="[559,816,1309,1334]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Pogostemon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="petelotii">
<emphasis box="[559,816,1309,1334]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Pogostemon petelotii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found in 
<collectingCountry box="[991,1095,1309,1335]" name="Thailand" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Thailand</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1169,1272,1309,1335]" name="Vietnam" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
. It grows in grassland in open places at elevations of 
<quantity box="[630,794,1348,1374]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" unit="m" value="1150.0" valueMax="1300.0" valueMin="1000.0">1000–1300 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="39" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,845,1954]" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,343,1386,1412]" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Etymology:</emphasis>
—The specific epithet “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Doan ex Gang Yao, Y. F. Deng &amp; X. J. Ge" authorityYear="2013" box="[627,723,1387,1412]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Pogostemon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="petelotii">
<emphasis box="[627,723,1387,1412]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">petelotii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” was originally proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Doan, T." box="[1075,1224,1386,1412]" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" pagination="915 - 1046" refId="ref2510" refString="Doan, T. (1936) Labiatae. In: Lecomte, H. (ed.) Flore Generale de L'Indo - Chine 4. Masson, Paris, pp. 915 - 1046." type="book chapter" year="1936">Doan (1936)</bibRefCitation>
for the species to be in honor of French botanist P. A. Pételot (1885–after 1940), who first collected the species in 
<collectingCountry box="[1274,1377,1425,1451]" name="Vietnam" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="39" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,845,1954]" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,340,1463,1489]" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Discussion:</emphasis>
—According to the classification of 
<bibRefCitation author="Bhatti, G. R. &amp; Ingrouille, M." box="[766,1078,1464,1490]" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" pagination="77 - 147" refId="ref2327" refString="Bhatti, G. R. &amp; Ingrouille, M. (1997) Systematics of Pogostemon (Labiatae). Bulletin of the Natural History Museum, Botany Series 27: 77 - 147." type="book chapter" year="1997">Bhatti &amp; Ingrouille (1997)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Doan ex Gang Yao, Y. F. Deng &amp; X. J. Ge" authorityYear="2013" box="[1090,1338,1464,1489]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Pogostemon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="petelotii">
<emphasis box="[1090,1338,1464,1489]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Pogostemon petelotii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to 
<emphasis box="[182,204,1503,1528]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">P.</emphasis>
subgen. 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Bhatti &amp; Ingrouille" authorityYear="1997" baseAuthorityName="Blume" baseAuthorityYear="1826" box="[310,444,1503,1528]" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Dysophylla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[310,444,1503,1528]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Dysophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Obviously, it is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuntze" authorityYear="1891" baseAuthorityName="Bentham" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[857,996,1503,1528]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Pogostemon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cruciatus">
<emphasis box="[857,996,1503,1528]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">P. cruciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from the latter by having the stems and leaves whitish adpressed tomentose (
<figureCitation box="[779,883,1541,1567]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,246,1862,1883]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,175,1818]" captionTargetId="figure-86@2.[151,1436,175,1818]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A. Holotype of Pogostemon petelotii (Pételot 1300, P); B. Isotype of P. cruciatus (Wallich 1541, K); C. Leaves of P. petelotii (Pételot 1300, P); D. Leaves of P. cruciatus (Wallich 1541, K). Scale bars: C, D = 1 cm. A and C reproduced with permisson by the Muséum National d'Histoire Naturelle (MNHN), Paris; B and D with permission by Herbarium of the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew (K))" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071557/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Fig. 1 C</figureCitation>
), leaf margins rarely revolute and sometimes dentate apically, midrib elevated conspicuously (
<figureCitation box="[725,796,1580,1606]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,245,1931,1952]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,462,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-196@4.[151,1436,462,1915]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Trichome morphology of leaves under scanning electron microscope and light microscope. Pogostemon cruciatus (G. Forrest 25140, IBSC): A. Trichome on the upper surface; C. Trichome on the lower surface; E. 2–3-cellular trichome. P. petelotii (T. Sörensen et al. 6313, KUN): B. Trichome on the upper surface; D. Trichome on lower surface; F. unicellular trichome. Scale bars: E–F = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071563/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) and lateral veins in 3–5 pairs (
<figureCitation box="[1168,1269,1580,1606]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,246,1862,1883]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,175,1818]" captionTargetId="figure-86@2.[151,1436,175,1818]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A. Holotype of Pogostemon petelotii (Pételot 1300, P); B. Isotype of P. cruciatus (Wallich 1541, K); C. Leaves of P. petelotii (Pételot 1300, P); D. Leaves of P. cruciatus (Wallich 1541, K). Scale bars: C, D = 1 cm. A and C reproduced with permisson by the Muséum National d'Histoire Naturelle (MNHN), Paris; B and D with permission by Herbarium of the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew (K))" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071557/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Fig. 1 C</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuntze" authorityYear="1891" baseAuthorityName="Bentham" baseAuthorityYear="1830" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Pogostemon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cruciatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Pogostemon cruciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the stems and leaves brown spreadingly hirsute (
<figureCitation box="[913,1019,1618,1644]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,246,1862,1883]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,175,1818]" captionTargetId="figure-86@2.[151,1436,175,1818]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A. Holotype of Pogostemon petelotii (Pételot 1300, P); B. Isotype of P. cruciatus (Wallich 1541, K); C. Leaves of P. petelotii (Pételot 1300, P); D. Leaves of P. cruciatus (Wallich 1541, K). Scale bars: C, D = 1 cm. A and C reproduced with permisson by the Muséum National d'Histoire Naturelle (MNHN), Paris; B and D with permission by Herbarium of the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew (K))" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071557/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Fig. 1 D</figureCitation>
), leaf margin usually revolute and quite entire, midrib inconspicuously elevated (
<figureCitation box="[703,804,1657,1683]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,246,1862,1883]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,175,1818]" captionTargetId="figure-86@2.[151,1436,175,1818]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A. Holotype of Pogostemon petelotii (Pételot 1300, P); B. Isotype of P. cruciatus (Wallich 1541, K); C. Leaves of P. petelotii (Pételot 1300, P); D. Leaves of P. cruciatus (Wallich 1541, K). Scale bars: C, D = 1 cm. A and C reproduced with permisson by the Muséum National d'Histoire Naturelle (MNHN), Paris; B and D with permission by Herbarium of the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew (K))" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071557/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Fig. 1 D</figureCitation>
) and lateral veins invisible (
<figureCitation box="[1142,1247,1657,1683]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,246,1862,1883]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,175,1818]" captionTargetId="figure-86@2.[151,1436,175,1818]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A. Holotype of Pogostemon petelotii (Pételot 1300, P); B. Isotype of P. cruciatus (Wallich 1541, K); C. Leaves of P. petelotii (Pételot 1300, P); D. Leaves of P. cruciatus (Wallich 1541, K). Scale bars: C, D = 1 cm. A and C reproduced with permisson by the Muséum National d'Histoire Naturelle (MNHN), Paris; B and D with permission by Herbarium of the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew (K))" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071557/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Fig. 1 D</figureCitation>
